---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="URL Encoder & Decoder"
  description="Encode or decode URLs and query strings online. Free URL encoding/decoding tool for developers. Supports UTF-8 characters."
>
  <div id="url-app">
    <div>
      <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Input</label>
      <textarea
        id="ue-input"
        rows="5"
        placeholder="Enter URL or text to encode/decode..."
        class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm font-mono resize-y focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500 focus:border-transparent"
      ></textarea>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-4">
      <button id="ue-encode" class="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-indigo-700 transition-colors">
        Encode URL
      </button>
      <button id="ue-encode-comp" class="bg-indigo-500 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-indigo-600 transition-colors">
        Encode Component
      </button>
      <button id="ue-decode" class="bg-gray-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">
        Decode
      </button>
      <button id="ue-swap" class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-gray-300 transition-colors">
        Swap
      </button>
      <button id="ue-copy" class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-gray-300 transition-colors">
        Copy Output
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="ue-status" class="mt-3 text-sm hidden"></div>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Output</label>
      <textarea
        id="ue-output"
        rows="5"
        readonly
        class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm font-mono bg-gray-50 resize-y"
      ></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 prose prose-sm max-w-none">
    <h2>Free Online URL Encoder and Decoder</h2>
    <p>Encode special characters in URLs or decode percent-encoded URLs. Supports full UTF-8 encoding. Essential tool for web developers working with APIs, query strings, and URL parameters.</p>
    <h3>Encode vs Encode Component</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Encode URL</strong> (encodeURI) - Encodes a full URI, preserving protocol, domain, and path separators (://?#=&amp;)</li>
      <li><strong>Encode Component</strong> (encodeURIComponent) - Encodes everything including separators. Use for query parameter values</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>When to use URL encoding</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Passing special characters in URL query parameters</li>
      <li>Encoding non-ASCII characters (Japanese, Chinese, etc.) in URLs</li>
      <li>Building API requests with user-provided input</li>
      <li>Debugging encoded URLs from logs or analytics</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How to Use the URL Encoder & Decoder</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3 text-gray-600">
      <li><strong>Paste your text or URL</strong> — Enter the URL or text string you want to encode or decode into the input field.</li>
      <li><strong>Choose the operation</strong> — Click "Encode URL" for full URI encoding, "Encode Component" for query parameter encoding, or "Decode" to convert percent-encoded strings back to readable text.</li>
      <li><strong>View the result</strong> — The encoded or decoded output appears in the output field below.</li>
      <li><strong>Copy or swap</strong> — Use "Copy Output" to copy the result to your clipboard, or "Swap" to move the output back to the input for further processing.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">What is the difference between encodeURI and encodeURIComponent?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">encodeURI encodes a full URL but preserves characters that have special meaning in URLs such as ://?#=&. encodeURIComponent encodes everything including those special characters, making it ideal for encoding individual query parameter values that might contain reserved characters.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Why do I need to URL encode special characters?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">URLs can only contain a limited set of ASCII characters. Special characters like spaces, ampersands, and non-English characters must be percent-encoded to be safely transmitted in URLs. Without encoding, these characters can break the URL structure or be misinterpreted by servers.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">How are spaces encoded in URLs?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Spaces are encoded as %20 in standard URL encoding. You may also see + used to represent spaces in HTML form submissions (application/x-www-form-urlencoded format). This tool uses the standard %20 encoding which is universally compatible.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Does this tool support UTF-8 and international characters?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes, this URL encoder fully supports UTF-8 characters including Japanese, Chinese, Arabic, and all other Unicode text. Each character is encoded as a sequence of percent-encoded bytes according to the UTF-8 standard.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is my data sent to a server when encoding or decoding?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">No, all encoding and decoding is performed locally in your browser using JavaScript's built-in encodeURI, encodeURIComponent, and decodeURIComponent functions. Your data never leaves your device, making it safe for sensitive URLs and API keys.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

<script>
  const inputEl = document.getElementById('ue-input') as HTMLTextAreaElement;
  const outputEl = document.getElementById('ue-output') as HTMLTextAreaElement;
  const statusEl = document.getElementById('ue-status')!;

  function showStatus(msg: string, isError: boolean) {
    statusEl.textContent = msg;
    statusEl.className = `mt-3 text-sm p-3 rounded-lg ${isError ? 'bg-red-50 text-red-700 border border-red-200' : 'bg-green-50 text-green-700 border border-green-200'}`;
    statusEl.classList.remove('hidden');
  }

  document.getElementById('ue-encode')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    try {
      outputEl.value = encodeURI(inputEl.value);
      showStatus('Encoded with encodeURI()', false);
    } catch (e: any) { showStatus(e.message, true); }
  });

  document.getElementById('ue-encode-comp')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    try {
      outputEl.value = encodeURIComponent(inputEl.value);
      showStatus('Encoded with encodeURIComponent()', false);
    } catch (e: any) { showStatus(e.message, true); }
  });

  document.getElementById('ue-decode')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    try {
      outputEl.value = decodeURIComponent(inputEl.value);
      showStatus('Decoded successfully!', false);
    } catch (e: any) { showStatus(`Decode error: ${e.message}`, true); }
  });

  document.getElementById('ue-swap')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const t = inputEl.value; inputEl.value = outputEl.value; outputEl.value = t;
  });

  document.getElementById('ue-copy')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(outputEl.value);
  });
</script>
